functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

functions.name: search
functions.desc: Search Wikipedia for an article with the given title, and get its content. If no such article is found, return similar article names.

chat_history.content:
Here is a summary of the Wikipedia article on 'São Paulo':

São Paulo is the largest city in the Portuguese-speaking world and is located in Brazil. It has a population of approximately 12,400,232 people as of 2020, making it the most populous city in Brazil. The city was founded on January 25, 1554, by Manuel da Nóbrega and Joseph of Anchieta and is named after Paul the Apostle.

The government of São Paulo is a mayor-council type, with the current mayor being Ricardo Nunes from the MDB party. The city covers an area of 1,521.11 km2 (587.3039 sq mi) and has an elevation of 760 m (2,493.4 ft). The metropolitan area of São Paulo, known as Greater São Paulo, has a population of approximately 22,001,281 people.

São Paulo is known for its diverse economy, including industries such as finance, commerce, and services. It is also a major cultural center, with numerous theaters, museums, and other cultural institutions. The city is home to several important landmarks, including the São Paulo Zoo and the Hospedaria dos Imigrantes, a historic immigration hostel.

In terms of infrastructure, São Paulo has a well-developed transportation system, including a metro system and a stock exchange. The city is also known for its efforts in sustainability and urban planning, with initiatives aimed at reducing pollution and improving the quality of life for its residents.

Overall, São Paulo is a vibrant and dynamic city that plays a significant role in the economic and cultural landscape of Brazil and the wider region.</s>

Here is a summary of the Wikipedia article on 'São Paulo':

São Paulo is the largest city in the Portuguese-speaking world and is located in Brazil. It has a population of approximately 12,400,232 people as of 2020, making it the most populous city in Brazil. The city was founded on January 25, 1554, by Manuel da Nóbrega and Joseph of Anchieta and is named after Paul the Apostle.

The government of São Paulo is a mayor-council type, with the current mayor being Ricardo Nunes from the MDB party. The city covers an area of 1,521.11 km2 (587.3039 sq mi) and has an elevation of 760 m (2,493.4 ft). The metropolitan area of São Paulo, known as Greater São Paulo, has a population of approximately 22,001,281 people.

São Paulo is known for its diverse economy, including industries such as finance, commerce, and services. It is also a major cultural center, with numerous theaters, museums, and other cultural institutions. The city is home to several important landmarks, including the São Paulo Zoo and the Hospedaria dos Imigrantes, a historic immigration hostel.

In terms of infrastructure, São Paulo has a well-developed transportation system, including a metro system and a stock exchange. The city is also known for its efforts in sustainability and urban planning, with initiatives aimed at reducing pollution and improving the quality of life for its residents.

Overall, São Paulo is a vibrant and dynamic city that plays a significant role in the economic and cultural landscape of Brazil and the wider region.</s>

functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

functions.name: search
functions.desc: Search Wikipedia for an article with the given title, and get its content. If no such article is found, return similar article names.
